<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 12:38:06 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>PV抑制性神经元，而不是整体前额皮质衰退，与可卡因寻求复发有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pv-inhibitory-neurons-not-overall-prefrontal-cortex-decline-linked-to-cocaine-seeking-relapse</link><description>毒瘾复发的风险极高，因为即使在停止吸毒很久之后，轻微的刺激也可能重新点燃毒瘾。此前，这种现象被归因于调节冲动的前额皮质（PFC）功能下降。然而，一个国际联合研究小组最近揭示，成瘾复吸的原因并不是简单的大脑功能下降，而是特定神经回路的失衡。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pv-inhibitory-neurons-not-overall-prefrontal-cortex-decline-linked-to-cocaine-seeking-relapse2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 12:38:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pv-inhibitory-neurons-not-overall-prefrontal-cortex-decline-linked-to-cocaine-seeking-relapse</guid></item><item><title>谷歌人工智能在乳腺癌检测方面与放射科医生竞争</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/google-ai-rivals-radiologists-in-breast-cancer-detection</link><description>对 175,000 名女性进行的关于人工智能在乳腺癌筛查中的应用的最新研究（迄今为止最大规模的 NHS 研究）表明，与人类相比，人工智能发现了更多的浸润性癌症病例，总体病例数更多，误报率更低，并且回忆起第一次扫描的女性也更少。在该研究的一部分中，人工智能将阅读扫描所花费的时间减少了近三分之一。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/google-ai-rivals-radiologists-in-breast-cancer-detection.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 12:23:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/google-ai-rivals-radiologists-in-breast-cancer-detection</guid></item><item><title>常驻巨噬细胞在维持小鼠眼压中发挥作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/resident-macrophages-play-a-role-in-maintaining-murine-intraocular-pressure</link><description>通过他们的研究，研究人员追踪了小鼠眼睛中荧光标记的常驻组织巨噬细胞。当他们有选择地去除这些细胞时，眼睛的引流管或流出道就会堵塞，液体积聚，眼压就会升高。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/resident-macrophages-play-a-role-in-maintaining-murine-intraocular-pressure.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 12:08:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/resident-macrophages-play-a-role-in-maintaining-murine-intraocular-pressure</guid></item><item><title>基于基因组测序的 CHIP 调用的性能特征及其对流行病学关联的影响</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/performance-characteristics-of-genome-sequencing-based-chip-calling-and-impact-on-epidemiologic-associations</link><description>我们是否需要更好的方法来检测不确定潜能克隆造血 (CHIP)？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/performance-characteristics-of-genome-sequencing-based-chip-calling-and-impact-on-epidemiologic-associations2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 11:53:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/performance-characteristics-of-genome-sequencing-based-chip-calling-and-impact-on-epidemiologic-associations</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局在不可能的地点发现极端恒星碰撞</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nasa-finds-extreme-star-collision-in-unlikely-spot</link><description>美国宇航局的一系列任务很可能发现了埋在巨大气体流中的微小星系中两颗超高密度恒星之间的碰撞。天文学家以前从未在这样的环境中见过这种类型的爆炸事件，这可能有助于解决两个悬而未决的宇宙之谜。一篇描述这些结果的论文即将发表在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nasa-finds-extreme-star-collision-in-unlikely-spot2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 11:38:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nasa-finds-extreme-star-collision-in-unlikely-spot</guid></item><item><title>解决蛋白质折叠中的屏障交叉问题</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/resolving-barrier-crossing-in-protein-folding</link><description>高时间分辨率荧光测量揭示了蛋白质穿过分隔未折叠和折叠状态的能量屏障的速度。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/resolving-barrier-crossing-in-protein-folding3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 11:23:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/resolving-barrier-crossing-in-protein-folding</guid></item><item><title>探索宇宙网</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/probing-the-cosmic-web</link><description>基于微扰理论的新数学框架可以产生对宇宙结构和基础物理学的新见解。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/probing-the-cosmic-web2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 11:08:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/probing-the-cosmic-web</guid></item><item><title>超快计算：光驱动逻辑在 WS2 中达到 10 太赫兹</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ultrafast-computing-light-driven-logic-tops-10-terahertz-in-ws%e2%82%82</link><description>我们计算机的未来将真正达到光速。极短的光脉冲可以执行超快的逻辑运算：这是最近的一项研究结果&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ultrafast-computing-light-driven-logic-tops-10-terahertz-in-wse282822.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 10:53:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ultrafast-computing-light-driven-logic-tops-10-terahertz-in-ws%e2%82%82</guid></item><item><title>混合合成策略解锁了以前无法实现的分子结构</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/hybrid-synthetic-strategy-unlocks-previously-unattainable-molecular-architectures</link><description>材料的分子尺度设计是现代科学的主要前沿之一。扁平、高度共轭的有机分子已用于化学传感器、光电器件和能量转换系统等先进技术中。提高其性能的最有前途的策略之一是将多个单元“连接”在一起，扩展其电子结构，从而改变其特性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hybrid-synthetic-strategy-unlocks-previously-unattainable-molecular-architectures2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 10:38:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/hybrid-synthetic-strategy-unlocks-previously-unattainable-molecular-architectures</guid></item><item><title>金和银原子接触中意外的磁响应与之前的理论预测相矛盾</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/unexpected-magnetic-response-in-gold-and-silver-atomic-contacts-contradicts-previous-theoretical-predictions</link><description>阿利坎特大学 (UA) 物理系和大学材料研究所以及马德里自治大学 (UAM) 低温高磁场实验室的研究人员首次成功测量了金和银原子触点在高达 20 特斯拉的极端磁场（强度相当于地球磁场的 40 万倍）下的电导率。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/unexpected-magnetic-response-in-gold-and-silver-atomic-contacts-contradicts-previous-theoretical-predictions2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 10:23:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/unexpected-magnetic-response-in-gold-and-silver-atomic-contacts-contradicts-previous-theoretical-predictions</guid></item></channel></rss>